title._content: Baggage at Albuquerque, New Mexico, waiting to be loaded on the Southwest Limited enroute from Los Angeles, California, to Chicago, June 1974

description._content: Original Caption: Baggage at Albuquerque, New Mexico, waiting to be loaded on the Southwest Limited enroute from Los Angeles, California, to Chicago. Amtrak is using airline techniques and other modern methods to expedite ticketing, luggage and other services in an attempt to upgrade facilities and attract passengers to use the railroads as an alternative to automobile travel, June 1974 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-13537 Photographer: O'Rear, Charles, 1941- Subjects: Albuquerque (New Mexico) Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: research.archives.gov/description/555989 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
